The paper deals with optimizing deep neural network architectures for dense semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Neural Architecture Search (NAS) also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses hardware-aware optimization, which could fall under the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for analyzing the results, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
